40|$|In renewal processes, {{fuzziness}} and randomness often coexist intrinsically. Based on {{the random}} fuzzy theory, a delayed renewal process with random fuzzy interarrival times is proposed in this paper. Relations between the renewal number and interarrival times {{in such a}} process are investigated, and useful theorems such as the elementary <b>renewal</b> <b>theorem,</b> Blackwell <b>renewal</b> <b>theorem</b> and Smith key <b>renewal</b> <b>theorem</b> in a conventional delayed renewal process are extended to their counterparts for random fuzzy delayed renewal processes...|$|E
